com.google.template.soy.parsepasses.contextautoesc

Enum Context.UriPart

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<Context.UriPart>
      • com.google.template.soy.parsepasses.contextautoesc.Context.UriPart
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<Context.UriPart>
    Enclosing class:
    Context

    public static enum Context.UriPart
extends Enum<Context.UriPart>
    Describes the part of a URI reference that the context point is in.

    We need to distinguish these so that we can

    • normalize well-formed URIs that appear before the query,
    • encode raw values interpolated as query parameters or keys,
    • filter out values that specify a scheme like javascript:.

    • Enum Constant Detail

      • NONE

        public static final Context.UriPart NONE
        Not in a URI.

      • START

        public static final Context.UriPart START
        At the absolute beginning of a URI.

        At ^ in ^http://host/path?k=v#frag or ^foo/bar?a=1.

      • MAYBE_VARIABLE_SCHEME

        public static final Context.UriPart MAYBE_VARIABLE_SCHEME
        After a print statement in the beginning of a URI, where it's still possible to be in the scheme.

        For example, after href=&quot;&#123;$x&#125;, it's hard to know what will happen. For example, if $x is "java" (a perfectly valid relative URI on its own), then "script:alert(1)" would execute as Javascript. But if $x is "java" followed by "/test.html", it's a relative URI.

        This state is kept until we see anything that's hard-coded that makes it clear that we've left the scheme context; while remaining in this state, print statements and colons are forbidden, since we don't want what looks like a relative URI to set the scheme.

      • MAYBE_SCHEME

        public static final Context.UriPart MAYBE_SCHEME
        Still possibly in the scheme, though it could also be a relative path, but no print statements have been seen yet.

        For example, between carets in h^ttp^://host/path or f^oo^/bar.html.

        This is similar to MAYBE_VARIABLE_SCHEME in that print statements are forbidden; however, colons are allowed and transition to AUTHORITY_OR_PATH.

      • AUTHORITY_OR_PATH

        public static final Context.UriPart AUTHORITY_OR_PATH
        In the scheme, authority, or path. Between ^s in h^ttp://host/path^?k=v#frag.

      • QUERY

        public static final Context.UriPart QUERY
        In the query portion. Between ^s in http://host/path?^k=v^#frag

      • FRAGMENT

        public static final Context.UriPart FRAGMENT
        In the fragment. After ^ in http://host/path?k=v#^frag

      • UNKNOWN_PRE_FRAGMENT

        public static final Context.UriPart UNKNOWN_PRE_FRAGMENT
        Not NONE or FRAGMENT, but unknown. Used to join different contexts.

      • UNKNOWN

        public static final Context.UriPart UNKNOWN
        Not NONE, but unknown. Used to join different contexts.

      • DANGEROUS_SCHEME

        public static final Context.UriPart DANGEROUS_SCHEME
        A known-dangerous scheme where dynamic content is forbidden.
